### Patch Information for CVE-2024-42094

#### Summary of Recommended Patching
The vulnerability CVE-2024-42094 relates to the `net/iucv` component of the Linux kernel. The recommended patch addresses the issue of avoiding explicit `cpumask` variable allocation on the stack.

#### Commit Details
- **Commit Reference**: [linux.git - kernel/git/stable/linux.git](https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux.git)
- **Patch Description**: The patch modifies the handling of `cpumask` to prevent stack allocation, which can lead to potential vulnerabilities.

#### Code Snippet
The following code snippet illustrates the changes made in the patch:

```c
// Original code with cpumask allocation on stack
cpumask_var_t mask;
if (alloc_cpumask_var(&mask, GFP_KERNEL)) {
    // Use the mask
    free_cpumask_var(mask);
}

// Updated code to avoid stack allocation
cpumask_t *mask = kmalloc(sizeof(cpumask_t), GFP_KERNEL);
if (mask) {
    // Use the mask
    kfree(mask);
}
```

#### Additional Information
- **Affected Component**: `net/iucv`
- **Patch Type**: Kernel patch
- **Patch Status**: Applied to the stable tree

